1
00:00:31,712 --> 00:00:35,072
=Love Actually S5=

2
00:00:36,799 --> 00:00:37,880
We can play frisbee now.

3
00:00:38,959 --> 00:00:39,319
Come on.

4
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:40,439
Go easy at first.

5
00:00:40,439 --> 00:00:40,959
Easy.

6
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:48,400
Can you catch it?

7
00:00:52,279 --> 00:00:52,840
Yeah, almost.

8
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:56,360
So close.

9
00:00:59,479 --> 00:01:00,639
You need to throw it flatter.

10
00:01:00,639 --> 00:01:01,759
Like this, babe.

11
00:01:01,759 --> 00:01:02,360
Throw it flatter.

12
00:01:02,360 --> 00:01:02,959
Like this.

13
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:04,760
Pancake.

14
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:05,160
Pancake.

15
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:21,959
Yeah, almost.

16
00:01:21,959 --> 00:01:22,760
That scared me.

17
00:01:23,639 --> 00:01:24,919
This seems dangerous.

18
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:26,400
Forget it, I'll step back.

19
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,552
(Running away)

20
00:01:30,559 --> 00:01:31,440
I'll just throw it to anyone.

21
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:35,584
(Afraid)

22
00:01:39,480 --> 00:01:40,360
Shall we take a walk?

23
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:43,360
The sun will set

24
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,000
very soon.

25
00:01:47,319 --> 00:01:48,160
Carry on.

26
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:49,360
We'll go for a walk.

27
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,239
Keep playing.

28
00:01:58,239 --> 00:01:58,599
Finally,

29
00:01:59,440 --> 00:01:59,760
cooling down.

30
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:00,839
Yeah.

31
00:02:00,839 --> 00:02:01,199
Feels good.

32
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:05,480
I thought we'd just play a little.

33
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,680
But

34
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:07,879
we really got into it.

35
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:10,880
But it was fun.

36
00:02:12,119 --> 00:02:13,160
It's good to exercise.

37
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:17,240
Oh no.

38
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:17,720
What's wrong?

39
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:18,600
My glasses.

40
00:02:21,119 --> 00:02:22,160
Your glasses?

41
00:02:23,839 --> 00:02:25,320
I forgot my silver glasses.

42
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:25,839
I forgot

43
00:02:25,839 --> 00:02:26,559
where I left them.

44
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:28,600
It's okay.

45
00:02:29,479 --> 00:02:30,839
Just run around blindly.

46
00:02:30,839 --> 00:02:32,600
I brought contact lenses.

47
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:33,839
So,

48
00:02:33,839 --> 00:02:34,839
which glasses are better,

49
00:02:34,839 --> 00:02:36,360
today's or yesterday's?

50
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,080
They both look good.

51
00:02:37,639 --> 00:02:40,279
The black frame

52
00:02:40,839 --> 00:02:41,360
is...

53
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:41,839
Business-like.

54
00:02:42,279 --> 00:02:42,520
No.

55
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:44,039
In the past few days,

56
00:02:44,039 --> 00:02:45,919
you weren't wearing glasses.

57
00:02:45,919 --> 00:02:47,880
Then you wore those black-framed ones.

58
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:48,880
It just feels...

59
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:49,720
Different.

60
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:50,399
Contrasting.

61
00:02:51,279 --> 00:02:52,320
Docile without glasses.

62
00:03:00,759 --> 00:03:01,520
The coffee is hers.

63
00:03:03,639 --> 00:03:04,080
Thanks.

64
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:05,720
Want to see my cooking

65
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,039
from when I first arrived in the UK

66
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:08,759
ten years ago?

67
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:11,759
I want to see what you looked like.

68
00:03:11,759 --> 00:03:13,839
(Curious)
Not exactly cooking though.

69
00:03:13,839 --> 00:03:14,199
Looks good.

70
00:03:14,199 --> 00:03:15,440
This is inedible.

71
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:16,320
This?

72
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:18,039
Looks questionable.

73
00:03:18,679 --> 00:03:19,839
Then later on,

74
00:03:19,839 --> 00:03:22,119
I made kimchi fried rice.

75
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:23,199
And some other stuff.

76
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,960
"Haven't cooked in a long time.
It's amazing."

77
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,919
Yeah, and I made udon.

78
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:32,360
At this point,

79
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,199
you started to improve.

80
00:03:33,199 --> 00:03:34,199
Yeah.

81
00:03:34,639 --> 00:03:36,199
I made egg waffles at home.

82
00:03:36,199 --> 00:03:37,399
You even bought a waffle maker.

83
00:03:37,399 --> 00:03:37,800
Yeah.

84
00:03:38,279 --> 00:03:39,679
What else did I make?

85
00:03:39,679 --> 00:03:40,639
I made quite a lot.

86
00:03:40,639 --> 00:03:41,880
Like shrimp head oil.

87
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,240
Singing alone at home.

88
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:46,679
Fried rice with shrimp head oil.

89
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:48,520
You think

90
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,039
you've changed a lot since then?

91
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,800
Since ten years ago?

92
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,559
Yeah, your style back then...

93
00:03:53,559 --> 00:03:56,880
I transformed my balcony.

94
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:58,399
Yeah, my balcony.

95
00:03:58,399 --> 00:03:59,039
So trendy.

96
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:00,080
I'd be alone,

97
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:02,000
sitting on the balcony, eating,

98
00:04:02,399 --> 00:04:04,199
watching the sunset and stuff.

99
00:04:04,199 --> 00:04:05,759
And I would put some fruit here.

100
00:04:11,119 --> 00:04:11,919
Tired.

101
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:13,199
Let's go back and rest.

102
00:04:14,199 --> 00:04:15,160
I can play badminton

103
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,000
for three hours now.

104
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:17,440
Impressive.

105
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,200
Two hours

106
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,079
isn't enough.

107
00:04:21,679 --> 00:04:23,000
We have a badminton group

108
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,119
in Shanghai.

109
00:04:24,119 --> 00:04:26,079
We play every Monday.

110
00:04:26,079 --> 00:04:26,799
There are many.

111
00:04:26,799 --> 00:04:27,959
There are many clubs

112
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:28,839
in Shanghai.

113
00:04:28,839 --> 00:04:30,480
Every club or court

114
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:31,839
has that kind of group.

115
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:34,399
You just pick a day of the week,

116
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,279
and a time slot.

117
00:04:37,079 --> 00:04:37,679
I was...

118
00:04:37,679 --> 00:04:39,160
But I've ignored their sign-ups

119
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:39,880
many times.

120
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:42,559
I would go.

121
00:04:42,559 --> 00:04:43,440
Playing with friends

122
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,799
is different from

123
00:04:45,799 --> 00:04:46,640
playing with strangers.

124
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:48,239
With strangers, you really play.

125
00:04:48,239 --> 00:04:48,640
Yeah.

126
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,399
You play seriously.

127
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:49,839
Yeah.

128
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,559
With friends, you're just

129
00:04:51,559 --> 00:04:52,519
fooling around.

130
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:53,000
But I think

131
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,519
I was playing seriously just now.

132
00:04:57,519 --> 00:04:58,519
Quite skilled.

133
00:04:58,519 --> 00:04:58,959
Alright.

134
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:06,559
Will you take a shower?

135
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:08,600
It feels cool in here.

136
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,000
Yeah.

137
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,119
I'll dry up

138
00:05:10,119 --> 00:05:10,559
very fast.

139
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,600
Let's head back now.

140
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:22,480
Should we buy some food?

141
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:23,000
Okay.

142
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,600
(Target)
Anything in mind?

143
00:05:24,839 --> 00:05:25,799
Do you still have coconuts?

144
00:05:25,799 --> 00:05:27,239
Can you open these coconuts for us?

145
00:05:27,239 --> 00:05:27,799
Or...

146
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,720
Open four coconuts for us.

147
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,279
Okay.

148
00:05:31,279 --> 00:05:31,559
Wait.

149
00:05:31,559 --> 00:05:33,320
Two iced, two room temperature.

150
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,399
Some girls might not

151
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:35,880
have iced ones
at that time of the month.

152
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:36,600
Let me carry them.

153
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,000
I'll carry some too.

154
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,279
You just stay pretty.

155
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:40,119
It's fine.

156
00:05:40,119 --> 00:05:41,040
Okay, thanks.

157
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:44,279
Let me.

158
00:05:44,279 --> 00:05:44,959
Give me that.

159
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:45,320
No need.

160
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:45,799
It's okay.

161
00:05:45,799 --> 00:05:46,559
Isn't it like

162
00:05:47,559 --> 00:05:48,279
weight training?

163
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:49,640
Mine are not heavy.

164
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:50,079
Give me one.

165
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,040
Take another one.

166
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,040
Give it to me.

167
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:57,959
What's this?

168
00:05:57,959 --> 00:05:58,760
It smells so good.

169
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:00,839
Flatbread.

170
00:06:01,239 --> 00:06:02,000
Flatbread.

171
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,920
What's inside?

172
00:06:03,559 --> 00:06:05,359
You can choose the filling.

173
00:06:05,359 --> 00:06:06,559
Want some?

174
00:06:06,559 --> 00:06:07,959
Is there a meat filling?

175
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:09,200
There are pickled vegetables and meat.

176
00:06:09,799 --> 00:06:10,839
Let's get some.

177
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,359
Four yuan each.

178
00:06:12,359 --> 00:06:13,279
Three for ten yuan.

179
00:06:13,462 --> 00:06:15,392
(Ready to go home)

180
00:06:17,679 --> 00:06:18,160
Is there

181
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:20,640
somewhere you want to go
but haven't been?

182
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:22,279
I've barely been to Europe.

183
00:06:22,279 --> 00:06:24,559
Just a trip to London and France.

184
00:06:25,079 --> 00:06:28,440
I haven't been to Germany or that area.

185
00:06:29,279 --> 00:06:30,040
I'd like to...

186
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:30,880
I like Spain.

187
00:06:31,559 --> 00:06:32,279
Me too.

188
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:33,799
And

189
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,440
I think Venice is nice.

190
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,119
Venice.

191
00:06:37,119 --> 00:06:39,000
There's a city

192
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,760
in Spain.

193
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:40,600
I forgot what it's called.

194
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,399
But that city

195
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:43,359
feels really energizing.

196
00:06:43,799 --> 00:06:45,239
Ibiza.

197
00:06:48,079 --> 00:06:48,679
Buy tickets.

198
00:06:48,679 --> 00:06:49,040
Let's go.

199
00:06:50,799 --> 00:06:52,000
The house looks amazing from here.

200
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,559
I haven't paid attention.

201
00:06:55,559 --> 00:06:56,519
Look at your sea-view room.

202
00:06:57,359 --> 00:06:58,200
So luxurious.

203
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,119
Now it's...

204
00:06:59,119 --> 00:06:59,519
Really.

205
00:06:59,519 --> 00:07:00,640
The center of the house.

206
00:07:10,399 --> 00:07:11,920
Should we make some rice?

207
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:12,480
Make rice.

208
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:12,799
Right?

209
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:13,119
Yes.

210
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,799
With that apron on,

211
00:07:16,799 --> 00:07:17,880
you look like a chef.

212
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,584
(The chef)

213
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,960
(Chef Xiao)

214
00:07:30,839 --> 00:07:31,880
Smells so good.

215
00:07:34,519 --> 00:07:36,119
Your hair looks so smooth today.

216
00:07:36,119 --> 00:07:36,760
Xiao Wentao.

217
00:07:38,519 --> 00:07:40,239
Suddenly a bit cute.

218
00:07:40,239 --> 00:07:41,839
Suddenly going for a cute look.

219
00:07:41,839 --> 00:07:43,399
(Cute Wentao)
Cute style today.

220
00:07:43,399 --> 00:07:45,160
Well-behaved.

221
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:46,000
Homey vibe.

222
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,968
(Homey-vibe Wentao is a must-have)

223
00:07:49,119 --> 00:07:50,640
You're actually quite photogenic.

224
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,239
Xiao Wentao.

225
00:07:52,399 --> 00:07:53,480
Come on, smile.

226
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,559
Come on, one, two, three.

227
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,920
That proud little smile.

228
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:00,679
It's amazing.

229
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:03,480
Here.

230
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,559
It smells amazing.

231
00:08:07,359 --> 00:08:08,040
Try it.

232
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,720
How is it, Xuan?

233
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,519
You like it?

234
00:08:15,079 --> 00:08:15,640
It's good.

235
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,119
Smells so good.

236
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:21,959
Impressive.

237
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:23,559
Awesome.

238
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,079
Great job, Xiao Wentao.

239
00:08:26,079 --> 00:08:27,200
Awesome.

240
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:34,000
So you actually cook often?

241
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,039
Not really.

242
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:38,239
I rarely cook
now that I'm back in China.

243
00:08:38,239 --> 00:08:39,239
Just getting by.

244
00:08:39,239 --> 00:08:40,640
I used to cook a lot when I was abroad.

245
00:08:40,860 --> 00:08:43,373
(Really)

246
00:08:46,799 --> 00:08:47,960
You know?

247
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:49,520
You doubted me before,

248
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,280
thought I couldn't cook.

249
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,359
Does anyone

250
00:08:51,359 --> 00:08:53,479
want to eat rice cakes or something?

251
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:54,479
Can you cook?

252
00:08:54,479 --> 00:08:55,440
You may like it.

253
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,119
Yeah.

254
00:08:56,119 --> 00:08:57,280
I can make some for you.

255
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,640
(Awkward)

256
00:08:58,640 --> 00:08:58,960
Yeah.

257
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,960
So I was completely wrong about you.

258
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:03,960
Completely wrong.

259
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,919
Any other assumptions?

260
00:09:07,039 --> 00:09:10,440
(Careful)
I dare not say anything rashly now.

261
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:11,880
Nothing.

262
00:09:13,359 --> 00:09:15,359
I haven't shown you the big dishes yet.

263
00:09:15,688 --> 00:09:16,479
(Impressive)

264
00:09:16,479 --> 00:09:17,320
What big dishes?

265
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:20,520
(Proud)
There are too many.

266
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:21,960
I can make a lot of things.

267
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,880
Don't tell them.

268
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:23,640
If you tell them,

269
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:25,479
I'll be the one cooking here every day.

270
00:09:25,479 --> 00:09:27,119
It'll become a cooking show.

271
00:09:30,359 --> 00:09:31,919
I saw you prepping the ingredients.

272
00:09:31,919 --> 00:09:34,599
(So smoothly)
And I realized that

273
00:09:34,599 --> 00:09:35,320
you could cook.

274
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:36,320
"This guy can cook."

275
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:36,960
He can cook.

276
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:37,960
"He can cook."

277
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:38,559
Yeah.

278
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,599
When you

279
00:09:40,599 --> 00:09:41,679
bought the rice cakes,

280
00:09:41,679 --> 00:09:43,640
why didn't you get anything else?

281
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,080
When I was buying those,

282
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:45,679
I thought

283
00:09:45,679 --> 00:09:47,520
we could add some random ingredients

284
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,320
we had at home.

285
00:09:48,799 --> 00:09:49,880
Then we came back,

286
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:51,200
and you were looking up recipes.

287
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:51,880
I was like,

288
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:52,960
"He's just learning now."

289
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:54,919
No, I've made it before.

290
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:55,960
I just forgot a bit.

291
00:10:02,479 --> 00:10:03,640
Time to check Moments.

292
00:10:04,512 --> 00:10:07,296
(Start checking Moments)

293
00:10:08,719 --> 00:10:09,799
Why are we so cool

294
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:11,760
about this?

295
00:10:12,799 --> 00:10:13,919
So chill.

296
00:10:13,919 --> 00:10:14,679
Relaxed.

297
00:10:15,679 --> 00:10:16,200
Indeed.

298
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,440
Acting like nothing's up.

299
00:10:21,919 --> 00:10:23,640
We're all good at pretending.

300
